nodes.text: The T'kkrpk were a species of sentient, long-lived insectoids. They did not begin to calculate time according to the Galactic Standard Calendar until their homeworld's Great Reconciliation circa 95 BBY; as a result, many of them did not know how old they were. Their language consisted of chittering and clicking noises. Their homeworld was defended by local defense forces, which included a female officer named T'Chttrk.
